title: Off-Topic for Vue but here are a couple of decent Nodejs tutorials
message:
For anyone else who wants to learn a bit about the fundamentals of Node (sans Express), I've come across a couple of decent tutorials.

This first one is a 90-minute Youtube crash course.  It's quick, but it's free and covers a lot of the basic concepts; I completed it in a couple of hours over a few days:

 

Node.js Crash Course

 

The second is a 34-hour Udemy course; so it costs money.  I started it this past week and it's been pretty decent so far:

https://www.udemy.com/course/the-complete-nodejs-developer-course-2/

 

Hope this can help anyone who wants to learn the basics of Node.

title: Vue Apollo Easy Call
message:
hey everyone, I created a github gist of an easy apollo vue call that you can do on the click of a button. Its fairly easy to set up but you need to make sure that before you can use it, you have apollo added to your project. To do that, its really easy:

 

  1. make sure you are in your vue project directory
  2. type 'vue add apollo'
  3. Answer N to both questions

 

You then should have a global instance of apollo that you can use in your project. Then using a click call is as easy as copying the gist I have and adding in your query from your playground. Reminder: this gist is a whole component, use it as a base template for creating a new component that you can add things on top of.

 

The link to the query gist is here:

https://gist.github.com/riderjensen/b6c5fd40244559925fc1bdc54117fa00

 

Mutations are a bit more complicated as what you need to do is declare a number of variables, then structure your query to use those variables. I have made an example in the below gist. Basically, you have a form, you bind those inputs so that your data is updating when the user types. Then you pass those data values as variables to your mutation. The mutation variables then are passed to the mutation text if you follow the correct naming conventions.

The link to the mutation gist is here:

https://gist.github.com/riderjensen/15158c17efeb357954d2d3dbd8a0b804

 

Let me know if you have any questions, the query is much easier to set up so that is a good place to start.
